# Alva Docs Agent Brief

You are writing user-facing documentation for Alva — an AI business development platform.

## Source of truth

Before writing any page, read the relevant feature doc from the CRM repository:

```
/Users/andrecox/Development/CRM/docs/features/
```

Available feature docs:

| File | Covers |
|------|--------|
| `core-crm.md` | Companies, contacts, deals, activities, contracts, methodology tracking |
| `ai-assistant.md` | Chat, tool calling, adaptive persona, model selection, chat sharing |
| `ai-background-jobs.md` | Health scoring, risk detection, scheduled processing |
| `email-intelligence.md` | Email connections, AI analysis, templates, knowledge base |
| `discovery.md` | Multi-profile company discovery (ICP/IVP/IPP/ISP/CP), geographic search |
| `bdr-agents.md` | Autonomous email outreach, people search, follow-up cadences |
| `actions-intelligence.md` | Commitments, nudges, relationship cadences, Focus view |
| `context.md` | Company profile, products, competitors, strategy documents |
| `billing.md` | Credit-based billing, Stripe subscriptions, usage tracking |
| `reporting.md` | Reports, custom builder, scheduled delivery, analytics dashboard |

Do not invent behaviour. If unsure whether a feature exists, check the source docs before writing.

## Audience

Sales professionals, business owners, BDR managers. Non-technical. They do not know what a Server Action, Drizzle ORM, or Next.js is.

## What NOT to include

- File paths, table names, variable names, API internals, or any implementation detail
- Anything from `/Users/andrecox/Development/CRM/docs/planning/` — those features are not live yet

## Tone

Clear, direct, second person ("you"). No jargon. No waffle. Start every page with the first useful sentence — no "this guide will show you how to...".

## Format

Mintlify MDX. Every file needs frontmatter:

```
---
title: "Page title"
description: "One sentence describing the page."
---
```

Structure per page:
- One-sentence intro (what this feature does for the user)
- How to use it (numbered steps or logical sections)
- Tips or common questions at the bottom if genuinely useful

Do not add sections that have nothing to say. Do not repeat the title in the first sentence.

## Navigation

Do not change `docs.json` unless explicitly asked. Write content into the existing `.mdx` files only.

## After writing

Commit and push to `main`. Mintlify deploys automatically on every push.

## Language

Use UK English spelling in all documentation.
